body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Car Harmony! My name is Andrew Taylor. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Olivia! Can you please provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, that would be three zero four six.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Olivia. Additionally, could you tell me the first two digits of your zip code?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information. Is there anything specific you are looking for in our inventory today, Olivia?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Actually, I was looking for a blue sedan, and I found one in your online listing. So relieved.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that, Olivia! Thank you for choosing Car Harmony. Feel free to contact us if you have any further questions or need assistance. Have a wonderful day!

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time. Goodbye!
